 <br>
So lets apply this &quot;nerf&quot; to only melee items. Is that fair? Will that balance the low end game? Will that make the low level zones more fun? Answers: No, No and not just no, but hell no!<br>
<br>
lvl 1 -10 bats, rats and yard trash<br>
lvl 10-20 desperately trying to get the hell away from the newbee zones.<br>
lvl 20-30 group tactics get developed and learning how to play your class begins. And if your lucky you make some good friends and start visiting a few dungeons.<br>
<br>
Ok, so lets apply this to all items. How about a plus 3 wis item that isn't useable until lvl 30? But wait, there are plus 5 wis items in lvl 10-20 zones. hmm, so maybe that wont work. How do we apply this to caster items?<br>
<br>
I have a neat idea, how about we let the players use their gear, yes THEIR gear, on any level character they want. If someone wishes to put a wurmslayer on a level one avatar, go for it. We all know that they will be bored after about two hours. <br>
<br>
Stopping twinking is not going to give players any more skill, at any level. Even with crap gear, lame players will still level.   <br>
<br>
It will not prevent people from powerleveling. <br>
<br>
It will not fix a single issue identified in all of the above posts. <br>
<br>
In fact all it will do is make the players who are too lame to get good gear happy, and do we need to make those players happy? <br>
<br>
The economy in everquest/on this server is interesting. But thanks to the influx of &quot;high-level&quot; gear, I have found that with a small amount of cash and a bit of patience I am able to get some really nice items. Am I wearing uber gear? no. Am I wearing gear that makes the twink haters jealous? no. I am wearing gear that makes this game fun.<br>
<br>
Items are challenge to get. It is what many people work very hard to get (myself included.) Don't just facking destroy all that because some lame ass cant do it to.  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65556>Rabican

